WEBVTT

00:02.168 --> 00:03.752
NARRATOR:
Previously on The Vampire Diaries:

00:03.920 --> 00:06.672
CAROLINE: Does Elena enjoy
having both of you worship at her altar?

00:06.840 --> 00:10.342
You can be in love with Elena all you
want if it means you'll protect her.

00:10.510 --> 00:13.512
He's flipped a switch. Stefan is gone
and he's not coming back.

00:13.680 --> 00:15.514
- Destroying Klaus is all I have left.
- You had me!

00:15.682 --> 00:18.767
- I lost you when I left with him.
DAMON: If I thought for a second...

00:18.935 --> 00:21.145
...I wouldn't have to feel guilty.
- For what?

00:21.312 --> 00:24.023
DAMON: For wanting what I want.
- I didn't plan on kissing him.

00:25.275 --> 00:30.029
Three sleeping Originals, four coffins.
Who is in the locked box?

00:30.196 --> 00:32.113
- Now I reunite my family.
- The people...

00:32.281 --> 00:34.241
...you cart around in caskets.

00:34.409 --> 00:36.201
You're doing this on my terms now.

00:36.369 --> 00:38.537
Rebekah. Kol. Finn, don't.

00:38.705 --> 00:40.330
KOL:
Aah!

00:40.498 --> 00:43.000
STEFAN: Coffin's open.
REBEKAH: Mother.

00:43.168 --> 00:45.627
- Do you know why I'm here?
- To kill me.

00:45.837 --> 00:48.589
To forgive you.
I want us to be a family again.

00:54.304 --> 00:56.013
MATT:
How's Mr. Saltzman?

00:56.181 --> 00:58.432
Resigned to spending the night
in Observation.

00:58.600 --> 01:01.351
So long as I promise to
change the lock on the house.

01:01.519 --> 01:06.273
So I talked to Bonnie earlier.
She and her mom are fine.

01:06.441 --> 01:07.983
Have you talked to Caroline?

01:08.193 --> 01:09.902
Yeah. She's holding it together...

01:10.070 --> 01:13.572
...considering how close
she and her dad used to be.

01:13.740 --> 01:15.991
Any word on who's behind
all these attacks?

01:16.159 --> 01:21.163
No. Sheriff Forbes said that
there's no real suspects at all.

01:22.707 --> 01:25.459
How are you dealing with everything?
I mean...

01:25.668 --> 01:27.753
You keep getting dragged into all this.

01:29.214 --> 01:31.256
Honestly? I'm kind of lucky.

01:31.424 --> 01:34.510
The only thing that I have
to worry about for tomorrow...

01:34.677 --> 01:36.720
...is showing up for my
shift at the Grill.

01:37.430 --> 01:40.599
Thank you for everything today.

01:40.850 --> 01:42.059
Really.

01:42.268 --> 01:44.186
Get home safe.

01:44.687 --> 01:45.854
Thanks.

01:48.483 --> 01:50.025
[SIGHS]

01:52.779 --> 02:08.877
[ENGINE STARTS]

02:12.632 --> 02:14.216
[THUDDING]

02:14.384 --> 02:15.425
What?

02:17.000 --> 02:23.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

02:29.816 --> 02:31.650
- Drive much?
- Rebekah.

02:33.403 --> 02:37.447
Surprised? You drove a dagger
through my back, Elena. It hurt.

02:38.158 --> 02:39.491
[ELENA SCREAMS]

02:40.910 --> 02:43.287
- Elijah.
- Leave.

02:44.372 --> 02:45.831
[PANTS]

02:48.918 --> 02:50.419
Are you challenging me?

02:50.712 --> 02:53.130
You're pathetic.

02:54.591 --> 02:55.966
Both of you.

03:03.224 --> 03:04.808
Well...

03:05.685 --> 03:08.103
...I believe we have
a little catching up to do.

03:14.444 --> 03:16.778
It was their mother Esther
who was sealed in that coffin.

03:16.946 --> 03:20.157
- As in the Original Witch?
- What? How is she even alive?

03:20.366 --> 03:23.368
Thought her freak of a son
ripped her heart out 1000 years ago.

03:23.578 --> 03:26.997
I don't know. I guess she has
connections in the witching community.

03:27.165 --> 03:29.791
Elijah said she wants
to live in peace with her family.

03:29.959 --> 03:32.252
- Including Klaus.
- She was to be the weapon...

03:32.420 --> 03:34.213
...to help us kill him.
ELENA: Not anymore.

03:34.380 --> 03:36.173
At least, not according to Elijah.

03:36.341 --> 03:39.301
That coffin was stopping
Klaus from tearing us to shreds.

03:39.469 --> 03:41.929
Anyone else
feeling a little used right now?

03:42.096 --> 03:45.557
Look, Elijah promised me that his family
wouldn't hurt any of us.

03:45.725 --> 03:47.267
[DOORBELL RINGS]

03:49.729 --> 03:51.480
I believe him.

04:07.372 --> 04:08.997
DAMON:
What is it?

04:10.625 --> 04:11.750
ELENA:
It's an invitation.

04:11.918 --> 04:14.628
"Please join the Mikaelson family this
evening at 7:00...

04:14.796 --> 04:18.548
...for dancing, cocktails and celebration."
- Who the hell are the Mikaelsons?

04:20.343 --> 04:21.510
The Original family.

04:22.053 --> 04:25.347
Not bad enough they're moving in,
now they want a housewarming gift?

04:26.099 --> 04:28.016
Wait, there's a note on the back.

04:28.351 --> 04:31.520
"Elena, I think it's time
that we finally meet.

04:32.563 --> 04:33.647
Esther."

04:34.023 --> 04:36.441
[OVER SPEAKERS]
This ain't no place for no hero

04:38.528 --> 04:40.737
This ain't no place for no better man

04:41.155 --> 04:44.032
Rebekah, tell me how handsome I am.

04:44.450 --> 04:46.451
Oh, Kol,
you know I can't be compelled.

04:46.619 --> 04:47.661
[DOOR OPENS]

04:47.829 --> 04:49.246
You went after Elena?

04:49.747 --> 04:51.873
- What is wrong with you?
- Here we go.

04:52.083 --> 04:54.835
- Want another dagger in your heart?
- Again with the dagger threats?

04:55.003 --> 04:57.921
- Don't you have other tricks?
- Go back to staring at yourself.

04:58.089 --> 05:02.843
- And who are you, my father?
- No, Kol. But you are in my house.

05:03.052 --> 05:05.220
Then perhaps we should go outside.

05:08.641 --> 05:09.891
ESTHER:
Enough.

05:11.144 --> 05:12.602
Niklaus.

05:13.438 --> 05:14.938
Come.

05:15.106 --> 05:19.067
This ain't no place for no better man

05:19.235 --> 05:21.069
This ain't no place for no hero

05:21.237 --> 05:24.614
Rebekah wasn't out of her box a day
before she tried to ruin my life.

05:24.824 --> 05:28.076
What happened to peace?
Acceptance?

05:28.286 --> 05:29.369
Family?

05:31.873 --> 05:34.082
You put daggers in their hearts.

05:34.250 --> 05:37.794
You want them to go on their knees
and kiss your feet for reuniting them?

05:37.962 --> 05:40.130
It's a crime to want us to be
as we were?

05:40.298 --> 05:42.007
You need to give it time, Niklaus.

05:42.175 --> 05:46.887
I've had a thousand years on
the other side to be angry and to heal.

05:47.305 --> 05:49.973
I'm here to make sure
this family does the same.

05:50.600 --> 05:53.226
I just don't understand.

05:53.978 --> 05:56.313
I killed you and still you forgive me.

05:59.525 --> 06:04.446
It's been my dream for a thousand years
that this family could be as one.

06:04.822 --> 06:08.658
Forgiveness is not a chore. It's a gift.

06:09.744 --> 06:12.829
Now, who are you bringing to the ball
this evening?

06:12.997 --> 06:14.206
[CHUCKLES]

06:14.374 --> 06:16.792
Don't be ridiculous.

06:16.959 --> 06:21.463
- You're lucky I'm even going.
- Well, I wish you would reconsider.

06:22.131 --> 06:24.674
It's going to be a magical evening.

06:24.842 --> 06:27.427
If Esther wants to talk to me,
I should find out why.

06:27.637 --> 06:30.472
That's a dumb idea.
She already tried to kill you once.

06:30.681 --> 06:34.226
No, Elena's right. Bonnie was led
to open that coffin for a reason.

06:34.394 --> 06:36.978
I think there's more to this
than some family reunion.

06:37.188 --> 06:40.399
Can we go back to the Stefan
who cared if Elena lived or died?

06:41.150 --> 06:43.485
What for? That's your job now.

06:46.155 --> 06:50.367
Stefan has a point, Damon.
I should find out what she wants.

06:50.535 --> 06:53.286
- You can't protect yourself.
- Okay, fine, then I'll go.

06:53.454 --> 06:56.331
You pissed off enough Originals
to last a lifetime. I'll go.

06:56.833 --> 06:58.417
- Hey...
- End of story.

07:04.006 --> 07:05.507
[CELL PHONE BEEPS]

07:08.719 --> 07:11.680
TYLER [ON RECORDING]:
Caroline, it's Tyler.

07:12.056 --> 07:16.184
I know I should have called sooner.
I just kind of freaked out and left.

07:16.686 --> 07:18.687
But I heard about your dad
and I'm sorry.

07:19.730 --> 07:22.691
I'm really sorry, Caroline.

07:23.067 --> 07:27.946
I'm out doing what he said. I'm gonna
fix myself and come home to you.

07:28.114 --> 07:29.739
I love you.

07:30.533 --> 07:31.616
[KNOCK ON DOOR]

07:53.598 --> 07:54.639
[SIGHS]

08:04.775 --> 08:06.067
[SCOFFS]

08:06.444 --> 08:07.986
Seriously?

08:14.285 --> 08:15.660
[SIGHS]

08:19.040 --> 08:20.332
ELENA:
It's all so weird.

08:20.541 --> 08:23.293
The Originals are throwing a ball.
Like, an actual ball.

08:23.461 --> 08:26.296
It's some twisted Cinderella fetish
is what it is.

08:26.464 --> 08:28.632
Why does the witch
want an audience with you?

08:28.799 --> 08:31.551
I have no idea.
But there's only one way to find out.

08:31.761 --> 08:34.429
I thought you told Damon and Stefan
you weren't going.

08:34.597 --> 08:38.683
I did. Which is all the more reason
I need a drama-free bodyguard.

08:38.851 --> 08:43.313
Well, I think a Salvatore would look a lot
better in a tux. And by that I mean Stefan.

08:43.481 --> 08:46.566
Ugh. I can't deal with either
of the Salvatores right now.

08:46.776 --> 08:50.403
Whatever Stefan feels, he's channeling
it all against Klaus. And Damon...

08:52.281 --> 08:55.492
- It's just not a good idea.
- Why? Because you two made out?

08:57.036 --> 08:58.703
Bonnie spilled the beans.

08:58.871 --> 09:01.873
I was gonna tell you.

09:02.083 --> 09:04.501
- After everything with your dad...
- Elena...

09:04.669 --> 09:07.128
...when you and Matt
kissed for the first time...

09:07.296 --> 09:09.881
...you called me
the second it happened.

09:10.049 --> 09:12.842
And I don't hear about this until now?
From somebody else?

09:13.010 --> 09:14.886
I'm sorry.

09:15.680 --> 09:18.306
It's just, I don't even know
how I feel about it yet.

09:19.475 --> 09:24.020
All I do know is that
it just used to be so much easier.

09:24.605 --> 09:28.316
Careful, Caroline. It's all well and good
till she stabs you in the back.

09:28.484 --> 09:32.028
What are you doing here? I know your
mom's rules. No murdering the locals.

09:32.196 --> 09:36.324
Get over yourself, Elena.
It's not all about you.

09:42.123 --> 09:44.124
[TALKING INDISTINCTLY]

09:45.668 --> 09:47.043
CAROLINE:
Oh, my God.

09:47.336 --> 09:49.754
She's inviting him to the ball.

09:49.922 --> 09:53.592
- Why is she inviting him?
- Probably to get this reaction from us.

09:56.012 --> 09:57.387
[CAROLINE SIGHS]

09:58.222 --> 10:00.181
What time is this stupid dance?

10:02.977 --> 10:04.978
[MUSICIANS PLAYING
CLASSICAL MUSIC]

10:10.776 --> 10:12.652
- Hello, Carol.
- Hello.

10:14.947 --> 10:16.698
Hanging out with your new besties?

10:17.199 --> 10:20.535
I'm the mayor, Damon. When the oldest,
deadliest family of vampires...

10:20.703 --> 10:23.663
...moves into your town,
you welcome them with a smile.

10:23.914 --> 10:29.044
Hmm. Well, at least you know who
you're borrowing that cup of sugar from.

10:29.420 --> 10:32.589
I'm trying to protect this town.
They assure me they want peace...

10:32.757 --> 10:35.717
...I've assured them that I'd enforce it.
KOL: Mayor Lockwood.

10:35.926 --> 10:39.054
We haven't formally met.
Kol Mikaelson.

10:39.221 --> 10:43.141
We hope your lovely town embraces us
just as much as we plan to embrace it.

10:43.893 --> 10:44.934
Damon Salvatore.

10:46.437 --> 10:47.562
Have we met?

10:48.314 --> 10:52.150
I've met a lot of people,
and you don't particularly stand out.

11:12.922 --> 11:14.130
Excuse me, Carol.

11:19.929 --> 11:22.389
- What are you doing here?
- I could ask you the same.

11:22.556 --> 11:25.433
Surprise, surprise. Nice tux.

11:25.601 --> 11:27.102
You're not supposed to be here.

11:27.436 --> 11:29.938
Well, I am.

11:30.272 --> 11:33.525
And I'm not leaving
until I find out what Esther wants.

11:33.693 --> 11:35.318
So shall we?

12:04.640 --> 12:05.974
Ugh!

12:08.102 --> 12:09.477
[SIGHS]

12:14.984 --> 12:16.985
[CHATTERING]

12:23.909 --> 12:26.077
[LAUGHS]

12:36.380 --> 12:37.964
Good evening.

12:38.591 --> 12:39.674
I need a drink.

12:46.182 --> 12:50.894
Elena Gilbert, I presume.
I'm Finn Mikaelson.

12:51.312 --> 12:53.396
You're here to see my mother.

12:54.315 --> 12:56.983
- Is she here?
- Her request did not include your friends.

12:57.151 --> 12:58.318
They're protecting me.

12:58.486 --> 13:01.154
You may not know,
but your mother tried to kill me once.

13:01.322 --> 13:05.241
If you want to see my mother,
you'll need to be alone.

13:06.577 --> 13:08.745
ELIJAH:
If everyone could gather please.

13:08.913 --> 13:10.830
MAN: Excuse me.
- Excuse me.

13:12.917 --> 13:15.919
Welcome. Thank you for joining us.

13:16.921 --> 13:21.049
You know, whenever my mother
brings our family together like this...

13:21.217 --> 13:24.219
...it's tradition for us to
commence the evening with a dance.

13:24.512 --> 13:26.638
- Do you see who I see?
- Oh, yeah.

13:26.806 --> 13:29.349
ELIJAH:
Tonight's pick is a centuries-old waltz.

13:29.517 --> 13:33.728
So if all of you could find yourselves
a partner, please join us in the ballroom.

13:40.945 --> 13:43.905
- Don't even think about it.
- She wants to see me alone, Damon.

13:44.073 --> 13:46.574
Sucks to be her, then.
Was I not clear this morning?

13:46.742 --> 13:48.576
- I was invited.
- You have to tell me...

13:48.786 --> 13:51.496
...before you go into a lion's den.
- So you can stop me?

13:51.664 --> 13:53.081
Yes.

13:59.588 --> 14:01.548
It would be rude not to dance,
you know.

14:06.554 --> 14:07.971
It is tradition.

14:21.986 --> 14:24.988
You look stunning, if it isn't obvious.

14:26.490 --> 14:28.241
Thank you.

14:51.223 --> 14:52.557
I'm glad you came.

14:53.851 --> 14:57.896
Well, it was either caviar
or sympathy casseroles.

14:58.063 --> 15:00.732
- I heard about your father.
- Don't.

15:00.900 --> 15:04.319
- Seriously.
- Very well.

15:04.528 --> 15:08.406
Onto more mannered subjects then,
like how ravishing you look in that dress.

15:09.283 --> 15:11.117
I didn't really have time to shop.

15:11.535 --> 15:14.537
The bracelet I gave you?
What's your excuse for wearing that?

15:16.749 --> 15:20.126
You know, you're quite the dancer.

15:21.795 --> 15:25.214
Well, I've had training.

15:25.674 --> 15:27.717
I happen to be Miss Mystic Falls.

15:28.594 --> 15:29.761
I know.

15:44.443 --> 15:48.780
Ooh. He dances.
And I didn't even have to beg.

15:48.948 --> 15:52.367
Well, Mayor Lockwood dragged me
out here. I couldn't exactly say no.

15:57.206 --> 16:00.667
What are you doing?
Why are you here with the she-devil?

16:01.085 --> 16:03.336
What was I supposed to say? No?

16:03.587 --> 16:05.380
Why the hell are you here with Klaus?

16:06.173 --> 16:07.590
[CAROLINE SCOFFS]

16:07.800 --> 16:09.092
Don't even get me started.

16:09.259 --> 16:12.095
Took you about 30 seconds
to put Damon in a mood.

16:12.262 --> 16:14.639
He's just looking out for me.

16:15.140 --> 16:18.351
I think he needs to figure out
that you can look out for yourself.

16:25.943 --> 16:28.820
- I need to talk to you.
- Okay, so talk.

16:30.656 --> 16:32.115
Not here.

16:37.329 --> 16:39.831
Stop staring. It's creepy.

16:39.999 --> 16:44.711
Of course she looks beautiful.
Nik gave her everything she's wearing.

16:46.463 --> 16:48.840
You're no dog yourself.

16:49.842 --> 16:52.010
- That supposed to be a compliment?
- Hmm.

16:52.928 --> 16:55.513
You tried to kill Elena last night.

16:55.681 --> 16:57.890
You don't get compliments.

16:58.058 --> 16:59.684
Caveman.

17:01.395 --> 17:03.021
Where is Elena?

17:06.650 --> 17:09.068
If Esther is secretly on our side,
we need to know.

17:09.236 --> 17:11.319
But I can't get to her
with two bodyguards.

17:11.488 --> 17:12.530
Why you telling me?

17:12.698 --> 17:15.700
Because Damon won't let me
anywhere near her without protection...

17:15.867 --> 17:19.704
...and you care about killing Klaus
more than you care about anything, so...

17:21.373 --> 17:22.707
What? Am I wrong?

17:27.921 --> 17:29.922
No, you're not wrong.

17:31.341 --> 17:32.425
What do you need me to do?

17:32.593 --> 17:34.802
Make sure I get into that room
with Esther.

17:34.970 --> 17:36.679
Alone.

17:37.014 --> 17:38.431
Are you sure you can do this?

17:39.683 --> 17:41.059
I can do this.

17:49.610 --> 17:52.695
When we were together, you used to
let me make my own decisions.

17:52.863 --> 17:54.280
You trusted me.

17:56.033 --> 17:58.785
After all of this,
at least that hasn't changed.

18:07.586 --> 18:09.253
Where's your date?

18:09.421 --> 18:10.797
Flirting with his ex.

18:11.590 --> 18:16.302
You've changed, Bekah. Settling
for mortals is the first sign of weakness.

18:16.512 --> 18:19.347
I'm not settling.
I brought him here to kill him.

18:19.515 --> 18:23.226
He's Elena's friend.
If he dies, she suffers.

18:23.393 --> 18:25.019
But I've already been scolded once...

18:25.187 --> 18:27.939
...so I was hoping
you'd help your baby sister out?

18:28.148 --> 18:30.316
And spit right in the face
of Mother's rules?

18:30.526 --> 18:34.612
[SUGAR & THE Hl-LOWS' "STUBBORN
LOVER" PLAYING OVER SPEAKERS]

18:34.780 --> 18:35.822
I'm in.

18:40.077 --> 18:43.371
I got your text.
What are we doing in here?

18:44.832 --> 18:45.873
[FLOOR CREAKS]

18:46.458 --> 18:47.667
[NECK SNAPS]

18:52.339 --> 18:55.299
Better hurry up,
won't be down for long.

19:13.819 --> 19:15.444
ELIJAH:
Elena.

19:15.612 --> 19:18.781
I understand my mother requested
to see you.

19:18.949 --> 19:22.618
Yeah. Why? Is something wrong?

19:22.828 --> 19:24.787
Well, her ability
to forgive my brother...

19:24.955 --> 19:27.290
...after everything he's done
to destroy this family...

19:27.457 --> 19:31.377
...strikes me as a little strange,
to say the least.

19:31.628 --> 19:33.588
Do you think that it's an act?

19:33.964 --> 19:36.799
It has me asking questions
I never thought I'd ask.

19:38.468 --> 19:41.137
Can I depend on you to tell me
what she says?

19:43.348 --> 19:44.599
Of course.

19:45.976 --> 19:47.977
I'll find you later. Okay?

20:01.200 --> 20:02.992
[KNOCK ON DOOR]

20:03.827 --> 20:05.870
That'll be the girl.

20:14.671 --> 20:16.339
FINN:
You're alone.

20:16.506 --> 20:18.674
Wise choice.

20:21.553 --> 20:23.054
It's only sage.

20:23.222 --> 20:26.682
I've spelled it so we can speak
freely without fear of being overheard.

20:27.184 --> 20:29.936
That'll be all, Finn. Thank you.

20:33.649 --> 20:38.027
You must have a million questions
for me, Elena. Please.

20:47.955 --> 20:49.580
How are you alive?

20:50.707 --> 20:53.376
- Are you a ghost, or?
- Not exactly.

20:53.543 --> 20:57.880
When I died, the witch Ayana
preserved my body with a spell.

20:58.173 --> 21:02.593
She was a close friend of mine,
an ancestor of your friend Bonnie.

21:02.761 --> 21:06.055
So that's why only Bonnie and
her mother could open up the casket?

21:06.223 --> 21:08.307
They complete the Bennett bloodline.

21:08.600 --> 21:10.810
I drew power from them...

21:11.061 --> 21:13.229
...and their ancestors with me
on the other side.

21:13.397 --> 21:15.940
You've been on the other side
for a thousand years?

21:16.108 --> 21:20.194
Nature's way of punishing me
for turning my family into vampires.

21:21.405 --> 21:25.616
But there is a way for me
to undo the evil I created.

21:27.494 --> 21:29.662
You're gonna help us kill Klaus,
aren't you?

21:29.913 --> 21:32.164
One thing at a time, Elena.

21:32.332 --> 21:36.002
For now, I simply need your help.

21:39.506 --> 21:41.090
[HORSE WHINNIES]

21:47.222 --> 21:49.348
You like horses.

21:51.768 --> 21:54.937
I'm not talking to you until
you tell me why you invited me here.

21:55.439 --> 21:57.523
I fancy you.

21:58.150 --> 21:59.358
Is that hard to believe?

21:59.526 --> 22:00.901
- Yes.
- Why?

22:01.153 --> 22:04.697
You're beautiful. You're strong.
You're full of light.

22:04.948 --> 22:06.032
I enjoy you.

22:06.241 --> 22:08.868
Well, I'm spoken for. By Tyler.

22:09.036 --> 22:10.745
And I thought you two ended things.

22:10.912 --> 22:12.955
Because of your freaky
sire bond with him.

22:13.165 --> 22:15.207
So you aren't spoken for.

22:16.168 --> 22:17.335
[HORSE WHINNIES]

22:19.671 --> 22:23.382
You know, horses are the opposite
of people.

22:23.550 --> 22:25.301
They're loyal.

22:26.928 --> 22:29.305
My father hunted me
for a thousand years...

22:29.473 --> 22:32.725
...and the closest he came was the day
he killed my favorite horse.

22:32.893 --> 22:38.272
He severed its neck with a sword
as a warning.

22:38.940 --> 22:43.819
Did you ever consider sitting down
with your father and talking it out?

22:44.071 --> 22:49.241
I'm afraid my relationship with my father
was a little bit more complex than yours.

22:49.701 --> 22:55.331
Maybe so. But I let my father go
with no regrets.

22:55.749 --> 22:59.168
And to answer your question,
yes, I like horses.

22:59.336 --> 23:05.007
But I also like people. And they actually
like me, so I'll be inside.

23:10.347 --> 23:14.433
I understand Rebekah shared
the story of my family.

23:15.227 --> 23:19.105
How I upset the balance of nature
by turning my children into vampires.

23:19.439 --> 23:21.941
She said you did it to protect them
from werewolves.

23:22.109 --> 23:23.776
It's true.

23:24.486 --> 23:27.947
But in no time at all
they began to feed on human blood.

23:28.115 --> 23:31.450
They ravaged the town
with no remorse.

23:32.244 --> 23:35.121
Eventually, Niklaus turned against me.

23:37.165 --> 23:40.251
How are you gonna kill him?
He's immortal.

23:43.755 --> 23:49.176
It will take time, magic,
and your assistance.

23:49.845 --> 23:51.470
What do I have to do then?

23:51.638 --> 23:55.683
My children believe I'm holding this ball
to celebrate our reunion.

23:55.851 --> 23:59.145
But in truth, I've gathered them together
to perform a ritual.

23:59.479 --> 24:02.982
The first step requires blood
from the doppelgänger.

24:03.900 --> 24:05.317
Only a drop.

24:05.569 --> 24:09.989
Its essence will be in the champagne
toast later on this evening.

24:14.661 --> 24:16.495
Will you do it?

24:18.832 --> 24:20.416
Or shall I?

24:43.023 --> 24:48.194
Elijah is more suspicious than the others,
so he may need more persuasion.

24:48.445 --> 24:52.239
But they must all drink at the toast
in order to be linked as one.

24:52.407 --> 24:56.577
- What do you mean linked as one?
- You said yourself Klaus can't be killed.

24:56.912 --> 25:03.709
But tonight's spell links all my children
together so that if one goes, they all go.

25:04.336 --> 25:07.046
- What?
- I love my family, Elena...

25:07.214 --> 25:10.216
...but they are an abomination.

25:11.051 --> 25:14.762
I betrayed nature when I created them.

25:14.930 --> 25:18.057
It's my duty to kill them.

25:23.813 --> 25:26.857
[MATHCLUB'S "BRAND NEW"
PLAYING OVER SPEAKERS]

25:27.025 --> 25:29.193
I'm itching to kill.
What are we waiting for?

25:29.361 --> 25:32.613
The mayor cornered me. Give me
15 minutes to lure Matt outside.

25:32.781 --> 25:36.617
Outside? What's wrong with here
on the stairs? Make a spectacle of it.

25:36.785 --> 25:41.288
You sound like an idiot, Kol. Mother
would kill you if you ruined her party.

25:41.456 --> 25:42.957
See you outside.

25:45.585 --> 25:46.710
[GROANS]

25:46.878 --> 25:51.048
Easy, buddy. I don't want you doing
anything stupid.

25:54.052 --> 25:56.762
- Where's Elena?
- Where she belongs. Talking with Esther.

25:57.013 --> 26:00.057
- What did you do?
- Don't blame me. This was all her.

26:00.267 --> 26:01.976
Right down to the broken neck.

26:02.143 --> 26:04.770
Maybe you shouldn't be such a
controlling dick, Damon.

26:04.938 --> 26:07.648
- Hang on. I'm the problem, here?
- You're a liability.

26:07.857 --> 26:09.441
I'm trying to keep her alive.

26:09.609 --> 26:12.027
Your emotions are getting in the way
of our plan.

26:12.195 --> 26:15.531
My emotions?
How is this even happening right now?

26:15.782 --> 26:18.492
Maybe because you care
too damn much.

26:25.292 --> 26:29.878
So, what are we doing out here?

26:30.046 --> 26:33.382
Just taking a break
from the polite chitchat.

26:34.968 --> 26:39.305
It's freezing. Let me get my coat.

26:39.848 --> 26:43.392
- This is your car?
- Yep.

26:44.686 --> 26:50.399
If I could compel myself a Maserati,
I would. But I can't.

26:51.443 --> 26:54.320
Oh, I'm a vampire. We don't...

26:57.198 --> 26:58.824
Thanks.

27:04.164 --> 27:08.167
Let's go back inside.
I've got all the fresh air I need.

27:17.344 --> 27:19.595
So how was my mother?

27:20.013 --> 27:21.805
Intense.

27:21.973 --> 27:25.351
And for what reason did she need
to speak with you in private?

27:28.438 --> 27:30.147
Elena.

27:30.357 --> 27:34.234
Should I be concerned about
my mother's intentions?

27:34.861 --> 27:38.864
She just wanted to apologize
for trying to have me killed.

27:39.032 --> 27:41.283
So it's true, then?

27:42.577 --> 27:45.079
She's forgiven Klaus?

27:45.538 --> 27:47.247
It's true.

27:47.666 --> 27:49.083
[GLASSES CLINKING]

27:49.417 --> 27:51.794
ESTHER:
Good evening, ladies and gentleman.

27:52.003 --> 27:54.254
Waiters are coming around
with champagne.

27:54.756 --> 27:58.050
I invite you all to join me
in raising a glass.

27:58.885 --> 28:01.595
It provides me with no greater joy...

28:02.180 --> 28:06.517
...than to see my family back together
as one.

28:07.686 --> 28:13.232
I'd like to thank you all for being part
of this spectacular evening.

28:14.150 --> 28:15.442
Cheers.

28:15.610 --> 28:17.820
- Cheers.
- Cheers.

28:26.788 --> 28:28.747
Cheers.

28:47.684 --> 28:51.770
So, what did you want to show me?

28:51.938 --> 28:54.857
- One of my passions.
- Oh.

28:55.024 --> 29:00.070
Impressive. I take it the curators
at the Louvre aren't on Vervain?

29:01.281 --> 29:04.032
Yeah, well, that's their mistake.

29:05.869 --> 29:09.246
And what about these?
Where did you steal this from?

29:09.456 --> 29:11.081
That's a long story.

29:11.249 --> 29:16.754
But rest assured it was worn by
a princess almost as beautiful as you.

29:19.758 --> 29:20.799
[SIGHS]

29:28.224 --> 29:31.602
Wait a second. Did?
Did you do these?

29:31.811 --> 29:33.395
Yeah. Um...

29:34.189 --> 29:37.065
Actually, one of my landscapes
is hanging at the Hermitage...

29:37.275 --> 29:39.943
...not that anyone would notice.

29:40.612 --> 29:44.573
- Have you been?
- I've never really been anywhere.

29:44.741 --> 29:46.825
I'll take you.

29:47.410 --> 29:51.997
Wherever you want. Rome, Paris...

29:52.207 --> 29:53.749
...Tokyo?
- Oh, wow.

29:53.917 --> 29:56.293
[BOTH LAUGH]

29:56.461 --> 30:00.631
Must be really nice to just snap
your fingers and get whatever you want.

30:01.716 --> 30:03.592
Is that why you collect hybrids?

30:03.760 --> 30:09.097
A little servant army to take
you places and bring you things?

30:09.265 --> 30:10.599
You're making assumptions.

30:10.809 --> 30:12.684
Then why do you need Tyler?

30:12.852 --> 30:16.313
Stop controlling him.
Give him his life back.

30:17.440 --> 30:19.149
You know...

30:20.151 --> 30:22.861
...this has been a fun evening...

30:23.112 --> 30:25.155
...but I think it's time for you to leave.

30:25.448 --> 30:27.241
I get it.

30:28.785 --> 30:32.287
Your father didn't love you
so you assume no one else will either.

30:32.455 --> 30:34.373
That's why you compel people...

30:34.541 --> 30:38.544
...or you sire them or
you try to buy them off...

30:38.753 --> 30:40.963
...but that's not how it works.

30:41.130 --> 30:45.133
You don't connect with people because
you don't even try to understand them.

30:49.764 --> 30:50.973
KOL:
There you are.

30:51.140 --> 30:54.810
I was waiting outside for you.
Where's Matt?

30:54.978 --> 30:56.979
About that. I, uh...

30:57.146 --> 30:59.982
I changed my mind.
I don't want to ruin Mother's night.

31:00.149 --> 31:02.192
Don't tell me you like this boy.

31:02.360 --> 31:05.821
And what did he do, he gave you
five seconds of his attention?

31:06.531 --> 31:08.198
Don't be so predictable, Rebekah.

31:08.366 --> 31:10.576
You don't have to be rude about it.

31:10.785 --> 31:12.578
Just leave him be, okay?

31:16.291 --> 31:18.417
As you wish, sister.

31:19.586 --> 31:21.295
Elena.

31:23.840 --> 31:26.425
- Did you get what you want?
- Actually, yes.

31:26.593 --> 31:28.552
Good. Tell me on the ride home.
We're leaving.

31:28.720 --> 31:31.680
No, Damon, let go of me.

31:31.890 --> 31:34.933
Look, I'm sorry that I had to cut you out
of the plan.

31:35.101 --> 31:37.811
There shouldn't have been a plan.
You shouldn't be here.

31:38.021 --> 31:41.023
Do you think I like
going behind your back? I don't.

31:41.190 --> 31:44.693
You would have tried to be the hero
and you would have ruined everything.

31:44.861 --> 31:48.864
Sorry for trying to keep you alive.
Stefan doesn't give a crap.

31:49.032 --> 31:53.827
- You're mad at me for including Stefan?
- I'm mad at you because I love you.

31:54.203 --> 31:56.872
Well, maybe that's the problem.

32:02.879 --> 32:04.546
No...

32:05.214 --> 32:08.592
...that's not what I meant...
- No, I got it, Elena.

32:09.135 --> 32:13.889
I care too much. I'm a liability.

32:15.892 --> 32:18.644
How ironic is that?

32:18.895 --> 32:21.271
CAROLINE:
Have you guys seen Matt?

32:25.610 --> 32:26.860
KOL:
Matt.

32:47.173 --> 32:50.133
Good evening.
You're Rebekah's friend.

32:50.301 --> 32:52.177
We haven't met.

32:56.182 --> 32:58.016
Matt Donovan.

32:58.267 --> 33:00.310
Kol Mikaelson.

33:01.187 --> 33:02.312
[BONES CRUNCHING]

33:02.480 --> 33:05.816
- Aah!
- Hey, hey, hey. Easy on the hand.

33:05.984 --> 33:08.276
The guy's a quarterback.

33:08.987 --> 33:10.278
[GROWLS THEN GRUNTS]

33:19.706 --> 33:21.289
STEFAN:
Damon!

33:24.210 --> 33:26.336
What are you, crazy?

33:29.674 --> 33:31.717
Maybe a little.

33:32.802 --> 33:36.054
Far be it from me to cause a problem.

33:47.608 --> 33:49.901
Tyler, it's me.

33:50.069 --> 33:55.782
Look, I'm grateful for
what you're doing but...

33:56.868 --> 33:59.036
...I miss you.

34:00.038 --> 34:03.874
And I really wish you were here.

34:20.266 --> 34:22.391
Seriously?

34:22.893 --> 34:25.645
Just give up already.

34:27.440 --> 34:29.024
[CHUCKLES]

34:33.737 --> 34:35.197
[SOFTLY]
Oh.

34:42.580 --> 34:45.916
No violence. That was all I asked.

34:46.083 --> 34:48.752
Rebekah and Kol disgraced
our family tonight.

34:48.960 --> 34:51.254
It won't happen again, Mother.

34:51.422 --> 34:53.297
I'll deal with them.

34:59.764 --> 35:02.140
Thank you, Elijah.

35:02.308 --> 35:04.851
I wish the others were more like you.

35:25.081 --> 35:27.207
Are we all right to speak freely?

35:27.708 --> 35:30.877
Yes. The sage still burns.

35:40.638 --> 35:42.389
Not having second thoughts, are you?

35:42.598 --> 35:46.643
Of course not. It's just Elijah.

35:48.187 --> 35:51.815
- He's so moral.
- You're doing the right thing, Mother.

35:51.983 --> 35:55.152
You understand what this means,
don't you?

35:55.653 --> 35:58.363
This spell I'm casting tonight...

35:58.531 --> 36:01.158
...will bind you all together as one.

36:01.325 --> 36:03.201
I understand.

36:04.495 --> 36:08.832
When it is time, I will be ready to die.

36:09.000 --> 36:11.001
Then we must complete the link.

36:27.393 --> 36:29.394
[SPEAKING IN FOREIGN LANGUAGE]

37:05.223 --> 37:07.557
The link is complete.

37:09.685 --> 37:10.727
You are one.

37:24.575 --> 37:26.493
So, uh...

37:27.703 --> 37:30.497
...Esther wants
to kill her whole family.

37:31.290 --> 37:32.958
How's that for Mother of the Year?

37:33.459 --> 37:38.088
Yeah. And I got to look Elijah
right in the eye and lie to him about it.

37:38.256 --> 37:41.132
Well, good. Can't say I'll be sorry to see
any of them go.

37:41.300 --> 37:43.260
I just signed their death sentences.

37:43.427 --> 37:47.264
No, you signed Klaus' death sentence,
Elena.

37:47.473 --> 37:49.599
Everyone else
is just collateral damage.

37:49.767 --> 37:51.768
It's not that simple.

37:52.603 --> 37:56.439
The family's brought you nothing
but darkness, Elena.

37:57.316 --> 37:59.442
It is that simple.

38:04.615 --> 38:07.284
So, uh...

38:07.451 --> 38:08.785
...where's Damon?

38:09.287 --> 38:12.122
I would think that he'd wanna make sure
you got home safely.

38:12.331 --> 38:14.541
I'll call him and let him know.

38:17.128 --> 38:19.004
What was with him going after Kol?

38:19.630 --> 38:22.507
Damon being self-destructive.

38:25.344 --> 38:27.971
I said something I didn't mean.

38:28.848 --> 38:30.807
So did I.

38:35.146 --> 38:37.397
Anyway, uh...

38:39.358 --> 38:41.276
Goodnight.

38:47.700 --> 38:49.492
Stefan.

38:52.830 --> 38:55.498
Did you really not feel anything?

38:56.792 --> 39:00.378
- When?
- How do you do that?

39:01.172 --> 39:06.217
Act like you don't care.
Like you don't feel anything.

39:06.427 --> 39:09.012
Because I can't do that. I...

39:10.097 --> 39:13.016
I feel. I feel everything.

39:13.184 --> 39:14.351
Elena, stop.

39:14.518 --> 39:16.519
I'm not going to stop, Stefan.

39:16.687 --> 39:18.855
Because I don't believe
that you feel nothing.

39:19.023 --> 39:20.899
You think I wanna be this person?

39:21.108 --> 39:24.736
I hurt you, Elena. I bit you.

39:24.945 --> 39:26.696
I hate myself for what I did to you.

39:26.906 --> 39:28.907
Then show it. Do something.

39:29.075 --> 39:33.745
Stefan, anything is better than trying
to convince me that you don't care.

39:34.246 --> 39:36.039
I can't.

39:39.877 --> 39:41.461
Stefan.

39:43.381 --> 39:49.219
If I let myself care, all I feel is pain.

39:57.645 --> 40:01.689
[SHE WANTS REVENGE'S "UP IN
FLAMES" PLAYING OVER SPEAKERS]

40:01.857 --> 40:03.566
Hi.

40:04.443 --> 40:06.319
What are you doing?

40:06.487 --> 40:10.615
Well, let's see, I went to a dance
and got my hand crushed.

40:10.783 --> 40:16.579
Found out I don't have health insurance,
so I just needed a minute to myself.

40:16.747 --> 40:20.375
Well, I thought maybe
I'd buy you an apology drink.

40:20.751 --> 40:22.919
Maybe you could just leave me alone.

40:23.379 --> 40:27.006
Look, I'm really sorry about Kol.
He's a lunatic.

40:27.591 --> 40:33.263
Look, Rebekah, you're really fun
and pretty and all...

40:33.806 --> 40:36.766
...but I really need you
to leave me alone.

40:40.771 --> 40:45.608
Burn. Rejected by the captain
of the football team.

40:46.277 --> 40:50.697
- Welcome to adolescence.
- Shut up, Damon.

40:50.948 --> 40:54.325
I knew I should have killed him.
Mother wouldn't let me.

40:55.703 --> 40:57.829
Well...

40:58.914 --> 41:00.957
...never let people tell you what to do.

41:01.125 --> 41:06.963
The canyons scream
And the alleys bleed at night

41:07.131 --> 41:11.968
Then the freeways fold
And the Santa Ana winds blow cold

41:12.136 --> 41:16.306
Besides, you would have broken him
in a second.

41:16.474 --> 41:18.391
Are you suggesting I can't be gentle?

41:18.559 --> 41:24.856
No. I'm just saying you should find
someone a little more durable, that's all.

41:25.316 --> 41:26.649
Together

41:26.817 --> 41:28.485
And who would that be?

41:48.756 --> 41:50.757
[MOANING AND PANTING]

